The paper deals with image alignment and interpolation using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial loss function for training the networks is also a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of machine learning for image synthesis and alignment, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization techniques for image alignment also involves the use of numerical methods, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of microscopy data, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
